<H1 align="center">Lists</H1>
Elements with a <span id="propinst-display" class="propinst">'display'</span>
property value of 'list-item' are formatted as other block level
elements, but preceded by a list-item marker. The type of marker and
its placement is determined by the list properties described below.

<div class="example"><P>
For example:

<PRE>
  &lt;STYLE type="text/css"&gt;
    UL         { list-style: outside }
    UL.compact { list-style: inside }
  &lt;/STYLE&gt;
  
  &lt;UL&gt;
    &lt;LI&gt;first list item comes first
    &lt;LI&gt;second list item comes second
  &lt;/UL&gt;

  &lt;UL class=compact&gt;
    &lt;LI&gt;first list item comes first
    &lt;LI&gt;second list item comes second
  &lt;/UL&gt;
</PRE>

<P> The above example may be formatted as:

<PRE>
  * first list item 
    comes first

  * second list item
    comes second


  * first list
  item comes first

  * second list
  item comes second
</PRE>
</div>

<P>In right-to-left text, the markers would have been on the right
side of the box. 

<H3>List properties</H3>
<DIV class="propdef">
<H4 class=propname>
    <a name="propdef-list-style-type">
       <span class="index-def" title="'list-style-type', definition of">
       'list-style-type'</span></a></H4>
<TABLE class="propinfo"><TR><TH align="right">Property name:<TD>list-style-type</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Value:<TD>disc | circle | square | decimal | lower-roman | upper-roman
  | lower-alpha | upper-alpha | none</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Initial:<TD>disc</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Applies to:<TD>elements with the <span
id="propinst-display" class="propinst">'display'</span> property set to 'list-item'</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Inherited:<TD>yes</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Percentage values:<TD>N/A</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>

<P> This property is used to determine the appearance of the list-item
marker if <span
id="propinst-list-style-image" class="propinst">'list-style-image'</span> is 'none'
or if the image pointed to by the URL cannot be displayed.

<P>The possible values have the following meanings:
<dl>
<dt>disk
<dd>A disc (exact presentation is UA-dependent)
<dt>circle
<dd>A circle (exact presentation is UA-dependent)
<dt>square
<dd>A square (exact presentation is UA-dependent)
<dt>decimal
<dd>Decimal numbers, beginning with 0.
<dt>lower-roman
<dd>Lower case roman numerals (i, ii, iii, iv, v, etc.)
<dt>upper-roman
<dd>Upper case roman numerals (I, II, III, IV, V, etc.)
<dt>lower-alpha
<dd>Lower case ascii letters (a, b, c, ... z)
<dt>upper-alpha
<dd>Upper case ascii letters (A, B, C, ... Z)
<dt>none
<dd>No list marker
</dl>

<div class="example"><P>
For example, the following HTML document:
<PRE>
&lt;STYLE&gt;
  OL { list-style-type: lower-roman }   
&lt;/STYLE&gt;
&lt;BODY&gt;
&lt;OL&gt;
&lt;LI&gt; This is the first item.
&lt;LI&gt; This is the second item.
&lt;LI&gt; This is the third item.
&lt;/OL&gt;
&lt;/BODY&gt;
</PRE>

<P>might produce something like this:

<PRE>
  i This is the first item.
 ii This is the second item.
iii This is the third item.
</PRE>
</div>

<DIV class="propdef">
<H4 class=propname>
    <a name="propdef-list-style-image">
       <span class="index-def" title="'list-style-image', definition of">
       'list-style-image'</span></a></H4>
<TABLE class="propinfo"><TR><TH align="right">Property name:<TD>list-style-image</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Value:<TD><span class="index-inst"
title="&lt;url&gt;"><span
id="value-inst-url" class="value-inst">&lt;url&gt;</span></span> | none</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Initial:<TD>none</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Applies to:<TD>elements with the <span
id="propinst-display" class="propinst">'display'</span> property set to 'list-item'</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Inherited:<TD>yes</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Percentage values:<TD>N/A</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>

<P> This property sets the image that will be used as the list-item
marker. When the image is available it will replace the marker set
with the <span
id="propinst-list-style-type" class="propinst">'list-style-type'</span> marker.

<div class="example"><P>
The following example sets the marker at the beginning of each list
item to be the image "ellipse.png".


<PRE>
  UL { list-style-image: url(http://png.com/ellipse.png) }
</PRE>
</div>


<DIV class="propdef">
<H4 class=propname>
    <a name="propdef-list-style-position">
       <span class="index-def" title="'list-style-position', definition of">
       'list-style-position'</span></a></H4>
<TABLE class="propinfo"><TR><TH align="right">Property name:<TD>list-style-position</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Value:<TD>inside | outside</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Initial:<TD>outside</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Applies to:<TD>elements with the <span
id="propinst-display" class="propinst">'display'</span> property set to 'list-item'</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Inherited:<TD>yes</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Percentage values:<TD>N/A</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>

<P> The value of <span
id="propinst-list-style-position" class="propinst">'list-style-position'</span>
determines how the list-item marker is drawn with regard to the
content. 

<DIV class="propdef">
<H4 class=propname>
    <a name="propdef-list-style">
       <span class="index-def" title="'list-style', definition of">
       'list-style'</span></a></H4>
<TABLE class="propinfo"><TR><TH align="right">Property name:<TD>list-style</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Value:<TD>
<span id="propinst-list-style-type"
		class="propinst">&lt;'list-style-type'&gt;</span> || 
<span id="propinst-list-style-position"
		class="propinst">&lt;'list-style-position'&gt;</span>
	      || <span id="propinst-list-style-image" class="propinst">&lt;'list-style-image'&gt;</span></TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Initial:<TD>not defined for shorthand properties</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Applies to:<TD>elements with the <span
id="propinst-display" class="propinst">'display'</span> property set to 'list-item'></TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Inherited:<TD>yes</TR>
<TR><TH align="right">Percentage values:<TD>N/A</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>


<P> The <span id="propinst-list-style"
class="propinst">'list-style'</span> property is a shorthand notation
for setting the three properties <span id="propinst-list-style-type"
class="propinst">'list-style-type'</span>, <span
id="propinst-list-style-image"
class="propinst">'list-style-image'</span>, and <span
id="propinst-list-style-position"
class="propinst">'list-style-position'</span> at the same place in the
style sheet.

<div class="example"><P>
  <PRE>
  UL { list-style: upper-roman inside }
  UL UL { list-style: circle outside }
  LI.square { list-style: square }
</PRE>
</div>


<P> Setting <span id="propinst-list-style" class="propinst">'list-style'</span>
directly on LI elements in HTML can have unexpected results.
Consider:

<div class="deprecated-example"><P>
<span class="example-title">DEPRECATED EXAMPLE:</span><br>
<PRE>
  &lt;STYLE type="text/css"&gt;
    OL.alpha LI  { list-style: lower-alpha }
    UL LI        { list-style: disc }
  &lt;/STYLE&gt;
  &lt;BODY&gt;
    &lt;OL class=alpha&gt;
      &lt;LI&gt;level 1
      &lt;UL&gt;
         &lt;LI&gt;level 2
      &lt;/UL&gt;
    &lt;/OL&gt;
  &lt;/BODY&gt;
</PRE>

<P> Since the specificity (as defined in the <a
href="./cascade.html#cascading-order">cascading order</a> is higher
for the first rule in the style sheet in the example above, it will
override the second rule on all LI elements and only 'lower-alpha'
list styles will be used. 

It is therefore recommended that 'list-style' only be set on the list
type elements:

<PRE>
  OL.alpha  { list-style: lower-alpha }
  UL        { list-style: disc }
</PRE>

<P> In the above example, inheritance will transfer the <span
id="propinst-list-style" class="propinst">'list-style'</span> values from OL and
UL elements to LI elements.
</div>


<div class="example"><P>
<P>  A URL value can be combined with any other value, as in:

<PRE>
  UL { list-style: url(http://png.com/ellipse.png) disc }
</PRE>
<P> In the example above, the 'disc' will be used when the image is
unavailable.
</div>

